In this exercise we will run a deepstream application on out jetsons

Today you are using the jetson nano 2gb kits (green ones). Note the differences.
a) you have to connect 2 wires, 1 datacable micro_usb to usba, another power cable (either usb c to plug, alternatively
usbc 2 usba on your laptop)
b) here the entire os is on the sdcard, so you do not need to mount or restart docker 
c)you will use userid: csed and password:  cslab768  to connect
d) I repeat dont try to mount sdcard or restart docker here
e) Once you are in the jetson device check whether you have the deepstream docker 
(You are looking for nvcr.io/nvidia/deepstream-l4t:6.0-triton)
You need to pull it if not present

f) Run your docker with the docker run command

In your docker check the folder
/opt/nvidia/deepstream/deepstream-6.0/samples/triton_model_repo/ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco_2018_01_28
It should have labels.txt, a subdirectory 1, and model file inside the subfolder 1. If it isnt there, download
the model (ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco) from below, create subfolder 1 and put it there
https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/master/research/object_detection/g3doc/tf1_detection_zoo.md

You can go through the video https://drive.google.com/file/d/1aP9lQeRCHeciRG38RPGDsYQrBF6FnvLA/view?usp=drive_link 
for steps to prepare the config files and run the application
